## Web Research Complete

**Queries**: 3 web searches + codebase audit executed
**Sources**: 7 authoritative sources found
**Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/c5a546036f24e673479649c4e6fa00d1/web-research.md`

### Key Findings

Most of the infrastructure for issue #286 already exists in the codebase. The key gaps are:

1. **Confidence display bug** — `PreferenceCard` reads `data.confidence` as a float, but the agent stores preferences as `{patterns: [{confidence: "emerging"|"moderate"|"strong"}]}`. All pattern-style preferences show "Emerging" even when they're moderate/strong.

2. **Weekly briefing "I Noticed" not rendered** — `preferences_learned: string[]` is populated by the backend and checked in `hasContent`, but the `WeeklyBriefingSection` expanded view has no render block for it. Needs a new UI block (and backend should return IDs to enable feedback buttons).

3. **Mobile feedback inaccessible** — "That's right"/"Not really" buttons are `opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100`, making them unreachable on touch devices.

4. **Toast missing hover-pause** — WCAG 2.1 SC 2.2.3 recommends pausing auto-dismiss timers on hover/focus. Minor gap.

5. **Chat referencing preferences** — Already handled via the reasoning agent system prompt (lines 308+). LLM-dependent, no code change needed.

### Gaps

- Backend weekly briefing returns `list[str]` (titles only) — needs Thing IDs to wire up feedback buttons in the briefing view
- No structural test coverage for preference toast triggering or confidence badge rendering

Sources:
- [React Aria Toast](https://react-aria.adobe.com/Toast)
- [LogRocket — Toast UX Best Practices](https://blog.logrocket.com/ux-design/toast-notifications/)
- [AI UX Design Guide — Confidence Visualization](https://www.aiuxdesign.guide/patterns/confidence-visualization)
- [Smashing Magazine — Psychology of Trust in AI](https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2025/09/psychology-trust-ai-guide-measuring-designing-user-confidence/)
- [Agentic Design — CVP Patterns](https://agentic-design.ai/patterns/ui-ux-patterns/confidence-visualization-patterns)
- [DEV — Accessible Toast in React](https://dev.to/hritickjaiswal/building-an-accessible-toast-notification-system-in-react-a65)
- [LogRocket — React-Toastify Guide](https://blog.logrocket.com/react-toastify-guide/)
